Quote:  ... countenance and told me that the young man Waitara [a2,a3-acute], was bewitched or <i>makutued </i>[a-acute]. I enquired how that event came about; he said, that an enemy of an opposing tribe had smoked out of the sick man's pipe, and he promised to show me what he could do in destroying the effects of the makutu [a-acute]; he accordingly approached Waitara, and began a shibboleth to the atua that no person present understood; ...
