Quote:  No doubt, had any of our people been taken ill and died, the belief would have been that they were `makutu' (bewitched), that is, that the god of their great Chief had entered the sick person and devoured him for violating his `tapu'.
Notes:  1856 Dec 31 T.S.Grace Report of Taupo District in Grace Pioneer Missionary (1928) 67

